==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carline thistle
<hw>Car"line this`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F. <ets>carline</ets>,
It., Sp., & Pg., <ets>carlina</ets>. Said to be so called from the
Emperor Charlemagne, whose army is reputed to have used it as a remedy
for pestilence.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A prickly plant of the
genus <gen>Carlina</gen> (<spn>Carlina vulgaris</spn>), found in Europe
and Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carlings</ent>⟦br⟧
